tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild normocytic anemia, decreased hematocrit, and impaired renal function (elevated creatinine). There is marked hyperbilirubinemia with normal liver enzymes, suggesting possible hemolysis or cholestasis. Metabolic acidosis is present (low arterial pH, low O2 saturation). Lipid profile is atherogenic (high total and LDL cholesterol). Urinalysis reveals proteinuria and glucosuria, indicating possible renal involvement. Further clinical correlation and follow-up are recommended.
